===Etymology===
{{etyl|enm}} ''[[talken#Middle English|talken, talkien]]'' 'to speak with, converse', frequentative of {{enm}} ''[[talen#Middle English|talen, talien]]'' 'to speak, recount', from {{etyl|ang}} ''[[talian#Old English|talian]]'' 'to suppose, reckon', from {{proto|Germanic|talōnan|lang=en}} 'to count, reckon' (compare Old Frisian {{term|talia|lang=ofs}}, German ''zählen'' 'to count', Danish {{term|tale|lang=da}} 'to speak'), from *''talō(n)'' 'talk'. More at [[tale]].
Frequentative ''[[-k#Middle English|-k]]'' suffix similar to ''hark'' from ''hear''. Akin to {{etyl|frs|-}} ''[[talken#Frisian|talken]]'' 'to chat', {{etyl|nds|-}} ''[[talk#Low German|Talk]]'' 'talk'.

